,"The temple servants: ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:46 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>The Nethinim</i>; also in verses 60 and 73"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Ziha, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Hasupha, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Tabbaoth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"the descendants of Keros, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Sia, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:47 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Sia</i> is a variant of <i>Siaha</i>; see Ezra 2:44."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Padon, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"the descendants of Lebanah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Hagabah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Shalmai, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"the descendants of Hanan, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Giddel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Gahar, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"the descendants of Reaiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Rezin, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Nekoda, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"the descendants of Gazzam, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Uzza, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Paseah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"the descendants of Besai, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Meunim, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Nephushesim, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:52 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Nephushesim</i> is a variant of <i>Nephusim</i>; see Ezra 2:50."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"},"the descendants of Bakbuk, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Hakupha, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Harhur, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54"},"the descendants of Bazlith, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:54 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Bazlith</i> is a variant of <i>Bazluth</i>; see Ezra 2:52."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Mehida, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Harsha, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55"},"the descendants of Barkos, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Sisera, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Temah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56"},"the descendants of Neziah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the descendants of Hatipha. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57"},"The descendants of the servants of Solomon: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Sotai, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Sophereth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Perida, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:57 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Perida</i> is a variant of <i>Peruda</i>; see Ezra 2:55."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58"},"the descendants of Jaala, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Darkon, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Giddel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59"},"the descendants of Shephatiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Hattil, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants  of Pochereth-hazzebaim, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the descendants of Amon. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:59 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Amon</i> is a variant of <i>Ami</i>; see Ezra 2:57."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60"},"The temple servants and descendants of the servants of Solomon numbered 392    in all. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61"},"The following came up  from Tel-melah,  Tel-harsha, Cherub, Addon, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:61 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Addon</i> is a variant of <i>Addan</i>; see Ezra 2:59."]}],"caller":"+"},"and Immer, but they could not  prove that their families  were descended  from Israel:  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62"},"the descendants of Delaiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Tobiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the descendants of Nekoda, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["642 in all.    "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"63"},"And from among the priests: the descendants of Hobaiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the descendants of Hakkoz, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the descendants of Barzillai who had married  a daughter of Barzillai the Gileadite and was called by their name) "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"64"},"These men searched for their family records , but they could not find them and so were excluded from the priesthood as unclean. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"65"},"The governor  ordered them not to eat the most holy things  until there was a priest to consult the Urim and Thummim. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:65 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>Lights and Perfections</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"66"},"The whole assembly numbered 42,360      , ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"67"},"in addition to their 7,337      menservants and maidservants,  as well as their 245   male and female singers . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"68"}," They had 736 horses, 245 mules,  ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:68 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Some Hebrew manuscripts (see also Ezra 2:66); most Hebrew manuscripts do not include this verse."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"69"},"435    camels, and 6,720     donkeys. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Offerings by the Exiles"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../exodus/38.htm#21|>Exodus 38:21–31</a>; <a href =|../ezra/2.htm#68|>Ezra 2:68–70</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"70"},"Some of the heads of the families contributed to the project. The governor gave to the treasury 1,000  darics of gold, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:70 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>1,000 gold drachmas</i>; that is, approximately 18.5 pounds or 8.4 kilograms of gold coins"]}],"caller":"+"},"50 bowls, and 530   priestly garments. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"71"},"And some of the heads of the families gave to the treasury for the project 20,000   darics of gold ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:71 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>20,000 gold drachmas</i>; that is, approximately 370.4 pounds or 168 kilograms of gold coins; also in verse 72 "]}],"caller":"+"},"and 2,200  minas of silver. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:71 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>2,200 silver minas</i>; that is, approximately 1.38 tons or 1.25 metric tons of silver"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"72"}," The rest of the people gave a total of 20,000   darics of gold, 2,000  minas of silver, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:72 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>2,000 silver minas</i>; that is, approximately 1.26 tons or 1.14 metric tons of silver"]}],"caller":"+"},"and 67  priestly garments. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"73"},"So the priests, Levites, gatekeepers, singers, and temple servants, along with some of the people and the rest of the Israelites, settled in their own towns. And by the seventh month  the Israelites  had settled in their towns. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Ezra Reads the Law"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../deuteronomy/31.htm#9|>Deuteronomy 31:9–13</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"At that time all the people gathered together  in the square  before the Water Gate, and they asked Ezra the scribe to bring out  the Book of the Law of Moses, which the LORD had commanded for Israel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"On the first day of the seventh month, Ezra the priest  brought the Law before the assembly of men and women and all who could listen and understand. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"So Ezra read it aloud from daybreak until noon  as he faced the square  before the Water Gate, in front of the men and women and those who could understand. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And all the people listened attentively to  the Book of the Law. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Ezra the scribe stood on a high wooden  platform built for this occasion. At his right side stood Mattithiah, Shema, Anaiah, Uriah, Hilkiah, and Maaseiah, and at his left were Pedaiah, Mishael, Malchijah, Hashum, Hash-baddanah, Zechariah, and Meshullam. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Ezra opened the book in full view of all the people, since he was standing above them all , and as he opened it, all the people stood up. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Then Ezra blessed the LORD, the great God, and with their hands uplifted, all the people said, Amen, Amen! Then they bowed down and worshiped the LORD with their faces to the ground. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"The Levites —  Jeshua, Bani, Sherebiah, Jamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodiah, Maaseiah, Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan, and Pelaiah —  instructed  the people in the Law as they stood in their places. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"So they read from the Book of the Law of God, explaining it ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>translating it</i> or <i>paragraph by paragraph</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and giving insight, so that the people could understand what was being read. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Nehemiah the governor, Ezra the priest and scribe, and the Levites who were instructing  the people said to all of them, This day is holy to the LORD your God. Do not mourn  or weep. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["For all the people were weeping as they heard  the words of the Law. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Then Nehemiah told them, Go and eat what is rich, drink what is sweet, and send out portions to those who have nothing prepared since today is holy to our Lord. Do not grieve, for the joy of the LORD is your strength. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"And the Levites calmed all the people, saying, Be still, since today is holy. Do not grieve. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"}," Then all the people began to eat and drink, to send out portions, and to rejoice greatly, because they understood the words that had been made known to them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Feast of Tabernacles"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../leviticus/23.htm#33|>Leviticus 23:33–44</a>; <a href =|../zechariah/14.htm#16|>Zechariah 14:16–21</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"On the second day of the month, the heads of all the families , along with the priests and Levites, gathered around Ezra the scribe to study  the words of the Law. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"And they found written in the Law, which the LORD had commanded through Moses, that the Israelites  were to dwell in booths ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>tabernacles</i> or <i>shelters</i>; also in verses 15, 16, and 17"]}],"caller":"+"},"during the feast of the seventh month, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"and that they should proclaim this message and spread it throughout their towns and in Jerusalem, saying, Go out to the hill country and bring back branches of olive,  wild olive, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>pine</i>; literally <i>oil tree</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}," myrtle,  palm,  and other leafy trees, to make booths, as it is written. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Leviticus 23:37–40."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"And the people went out, brought back branches, and made  booths on their own rooftops, in their courtyards, in the courts of the house of God, and in the squares by the Water Gate and by the Gate of Ephraim. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"The whole assembly that had returned from exile made booths and lived in them.  From the days of Joshua ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>Jeshua</i>, a variant of <i>Joshua</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"son of Nun until that day, the Israelites  had not celebrated like this. And there was great rejoicing. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Day after day, from the first day to the last, Ezra read from the Book of the Law of God. The Israelites kept the feast for seven days, and on the eighth day  they held an assembly, according to the ordinance. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The People Confess Their Sins"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"On the twenty-fourth  day of the same month, the Israelites  gathered together, fasting and wearing sackcloth, with dust on their heads. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Those of Israelite descent separated themselves from all the foreigners , and they stood and confessed  their sins and the iniquities of their fathers. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"While they stood in their places, they read from the Book of the Law of the LORD their God for a quarter of the day, and they spent another quarter of the day in confession and worship of the LORD their God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"And the Levites —  Jeshua, Bani, Kadmiel, Shebaniah, Bunni, Sherebiah, Bani, and Chenani —  stood on the raised platform and cried out in a loud voice to the LORD their God. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Then the Levites— Jeshua, Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabneiah, Sherebiah, Hodiah, Shebaniah, and Pethahiah— said, Stand up and bless  the LORD your God from everlasting to everlasting: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Blessed be Your glorious name, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and may it be exalted "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["above all blessing and praise. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"You  alone  are the LORD. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You created  the heavens, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the highest heavens  with all their host, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the earth and all that is on it, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the seas and all that is in them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You give life  to all things, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and the host of heaven worships You. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"You  are the LORD, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the God who chose Abram, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who brought him out of Ur of the Chaldeans "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and gave him the name Abraham. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"You found  his heart faithful before You, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and made a covenant with him "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to give  the land of the Canaanites and Hittites, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of the Amorites and Perizzites, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of the Jebusites and Girgashites— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to give it to his descendants. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You have kept  Your promise, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because You are righteous. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"You saw  the affliction of our fathers in Egypt; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" You heard their cry at the Red Sea. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the Sea of Reeds</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"You performed signs and wonders against Pharaoh, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["all his officials, and all the people of his land, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for You knew  they had acted with arrogance "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["against our fathers. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You made a name for Yourself "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that endures to this day. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"You divided the sea before them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and they crossed through it on dry ground.  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You hurled their pursuers into the depths "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like a stone into raging waters . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"You led them with a pillar of cloud by day "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and a pillar of fire by night, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to light for them the way "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in which they should travel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"You came down on Mount Sinai "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and spoke with them from heaven. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You gave them just ordinances, true laws, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and good statutes and commandments. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"}," You revealed to them Your holy Sabbath "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and gave them commandments and statutes and laws "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["through Your servant Moses. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"In their hunger You gave them bread from heaven; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in their thirst You brought them water from the rock. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You told them to go in and possess  the land "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that You had sworn   to give them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"But they and our fathers became arrogant and stiff-necked   "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and did not obey  Your commandments. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"They refused to listen and failed to remember "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["the wonders  You performed among them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They stiffened  their necks and appointed a leader "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to return them to their bondage in Egypt. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["LXX and a few Hebrew manuscripts; MT <i>to return them to their bondage in their rebellion</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But You are a forgiving God, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["gracious and compassionate, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["slow to anger and rich in loving devotion, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and You did not forsake them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Even when they cast for themselves "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["an image of a calf and said, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["This is your God who brought you up out of Egypt, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and when they committed terrible blasphemies, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"You in Your great compassion "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["did not forsake them in the wilderness . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["By day the pillar of cloud never turned away "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" from guiding them on their path;  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and by the night the pillar of fire "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["illuminated  the way  they should go. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"You gave Your good Spirit to instruct them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You did not withhold Your manna from their mouths, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and You gave them water for their thirst. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For forty years You sustained them in the wilderness, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so that they lacked nothing. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Their clothes did not wear out "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and their feet did not swell. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"You gave them kingdoms and peoples "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and allotted to them every corner of the land. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So they took  the land of Sihon ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["One Hebrew manuscript and LXX; most Hebrew manuscripts <i>Sihon, the country of the</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}," king of Heshbon  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and of Og king of Bashan. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"You multiplied their descendants "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["like the stars of heaven "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and brought them to the land  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You had told their fathers to enter and possess. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"So their descendants went in and possessed  the land; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You subdued before them  the Canaanites dwelling in the land. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You delivered into their hands  the kings and peoples of the land, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to do with them as they wished. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"They captured fortified cities  and fertile land "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and took houses full of all goods, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["wells already dug, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["vineyards, olive groves, and fruit trees in abundance. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So they ate and were filled; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they grew fat and delighted in Your great goodness. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"But they were disobedient and rebelled against You; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they flung  Your law behind their backs. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[" They killed Your prophets, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who had admonished them to return to You. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They committed terrible blasphemies. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"So You delivered them into the hands "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of enemies who oppressed them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and in their time of distress they cried out to You. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["From heaven You heard them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and in Your great compassion You gave them deliverers "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who saved them from the hands of their enemies. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"But as soon as they had rest "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they again did evil in Your sight. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So You abandoned them to the hands of their enemies, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who had dominion over them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When they cried out to You again, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You heard from heaven, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and You delivered them many times "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in Your compassion. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"You admonished them to turn back to Your law, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["but they were arrogant  and disobeyed Your commandments. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They sinned against Your ordinances, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["by which a man will live if he practices them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They turned a stubborn shoulder; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they stiffened their necks and would not obey. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"You were patient with them for many years, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and Your Spirit admonished them through Your prophets. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Yet they would not listen, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["so You gave them into the hands of the neighboring peoples . ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:30 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally <i>into the hands of the peoples of the lands</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"But in Your great compassion, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You did not put an end to them ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["nor did You forsake them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for You are a gracious and compassionate God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"So now, our God, the great and mighty and awesome God "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who keeps His gracious covenant, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["do not view lightly   all the hardship "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that has come upon us, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and upon our kings and leaders, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["our priests and prophets, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["our ancestors and all Your people, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["from the days of the kings of Assyria until today  . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"You are just in all that has befallen us, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because You have acted faithfully, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["while we have acted wickedly. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"}," Our kings and leaders and priests and fathers "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["did not obey Your law  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or listen to Your commandments "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and warnings that You gave them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"For even while they were in their kingdom, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["with the abundant goodness "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that You had given them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and in the spacious and fertile land "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["that You had set before them, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["they would not serve You  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["or turn from their wicked ways. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"So here we are today as slaves "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["in the land  You gave our fathers to enjoy  its fruit  and goodness— "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["here  we are as slaves! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Its abundant harvest goes to the kings  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["You have set over us because of our sins. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And they rule over our bodies and our livestock as they please. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["We are in great distress. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"In view of all this, we make a binding agreement, putting it in writing and sealing it with the names of ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:38 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew does not include <i>the names of</i>."]}],"caller":"+"},"our leaders, Levites, and priests. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Signers of the Covenant"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Now these were the ones who sealed the document: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Nehemiah the governor, son of Hacaliah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and also Zedekiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Pashhur, Amariah, Malchijah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Hattush, Shebaniah, Malluch, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Harim, Meremoth, Obadiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Meshullam, Abijah, Mijamin, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Maaziah, Bilgai, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Bilgai</i> is a variant of <i>Bilgah</i>; see Nehemiah 12:5."]}],"caller":"+"},"and Shemaiah. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["These were the priests. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"The Levites: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jeshua son of Azaniah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Binnui of the sons of Henadad, Kadmiel, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"and their associates: Shebaniah, Hodiah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Mica, Rehob, Hashabiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Hodiah, Bani, and Beninu. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"And the leaders of the people: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Parosh,  Pahath-moab, Elam, Zattu, Bani, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Bunni, Azgad, Bebai, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Adonijah, Bigvai, Adin, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Ater, Hezekiah, Azzur, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Hodiah, Hashum, Bezai, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Hariph, Anathoth, Nebai, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Magpiash, Meshullam, Hezir, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Meshezabel, Zadok, Jaddua, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Pelatiah, Hanan, Anaiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Hoshea, Hananiah, Hasshub, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Hallohesh, Pilha, Shobek, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Rehum, Hashabnah, Maaseiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Ahijah, Hanan, Anan, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Malluch, Harim, and Baanah. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Vows of the Covenant"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"The rest of the people— the priests, Levites, gatekeepers, singers, temple servants, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:28 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>Nethinim</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"and all who had separated themselves from the people of the land to obey the Law of God— along with their wives and all their sons and daughters  who are able to understand, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"hereby join with their noble brothers and commit themselves with a sworn oath to follow the Law of God  given through His servant Moses and to obey carefully  all the commandments, ordinances, and statutes of the LORD our Lord. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"}," We will not give our daughters in marriage to the people of the land,  and we will not take their daughters for our sons. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"When the people of the land bring  merchandise or any kind of grain to sell on the Sabbath day, we will not buy from them on a Sabbath or holy day. Every seventh year we will let the fields lie fallow  and will cancel every  debt. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"We also place ourselves under the obligation to contribute a third of a shekel ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:32 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>A third of a shekel</i> is approximately 0.13 ounces or 3.8 grams, probably of silver."]}],"caller":"+"},"yearly for the service of the house of our God: ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"for the showbread , for the regular grain offerings  and burnt offerings, for the Sabbath offerings, for the New Moons and appointed feasts, for the holy offerings, for the sin offerings to make atonement for Israel, and for all the duties of the house of our God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"We have cast lots among the priests, Levites, and people for the donation of wood by our families  at the appointed times each year . They are to bring it to the house of our God to burn on the altar of the LORD our God, as it is written in the Law. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"We will also bring  the firstfruits of our land  and of every fruit  tree to the house of the LORD year by year. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"And we will bring the firstborn of our sons and our livestock, as it is written in the Law, and will bring the firstborn of our herds and flocks to the house of our God, to the priests who minister in the house of our God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Moreover, we will bring to the priests at the storerooms of the house of our God the firstfruits of our dough, of our grain offerings, of the fruit of all our trees, and of our new wine and oil. A tenth of our produce belongs to the Levites, so that they  shall receive tithes in all the towns where we labor. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"A priest of Aaron’s line is to accompany  the Levites when they collect the tenth, and the Levites are to bring  a tenth of these tithes to the storerooms of the treasury  in the house of our God. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"For the Israelites  and the Levites   are to bring the contributions of grain, new wine, and oil to the storerooms where the articles of the sanctuary are kept and where the ministering priests, the gatekeepers, and the singers stay. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Thus we will not neglect  the house of our God. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Jerusalem’s New Settlers"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Now the leaders of the people settled in Jerusalem, and the rest of the people cast lots to bring one out of ten to live in the holy city of Jerusalem, while the remaining nine ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>nine hands</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"were to dwell in their own towns. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"And the people blessed all the men who volunteered to live in Jerusalem. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"These are the heads of the provinces who settled in Jerusalem. (In the villages of Judah, however, each lived on his own property in their towns— the Israelites, priests, Levites, temple servants, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>Nethinim</i>; also in verse 21"]}],"caller":"+"},"and descendants of Solomon’s servants— ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"while some of the descendants of Judah and Benjamin settled in Jerusalem. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["From the descendants  of Judah: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Athaiah son of Uzziah, the son of Zechariah, the son of Amariah, the son of Shephatiah, the son of Mahalalel, a descendant of Perez; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"and Maaseiah son of Baruch, the son  of Col-hozeh, the son of Hazaiah, the son of Adaiah, the son of Joiarib, the son of Zechariah, a descendant of Shelah. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>of the Shilonite</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"The descendants of Perez who settled in Jerusalem totaled 468    men of valor. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"From the descendants of Benjamin: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Sallu son of Meshullam, the son of Joed, the son of Pedaiah, the son of Kolaiah, the son of Maaseiah, the son of Ithiel, the son of Jeshaiah; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"and his followers Gabbai and Sallai —  928 men   . ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Joel son of Zichri was the officer over them, and Judah son of Hassenuah was over the Second District of the city. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:9 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>was over the Second Quarter of the city</i>, a newer section of Jerusalem; or <i>was second in command of the city</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"From the priests: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jedaiah son of Joiarib; ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>Jedaiah; the son of Joiarib;</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"Jachin; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Seraiah son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, the chief official of the house of God; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"and their associates who did the work at the temple —  822 men   ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Adaiah son of Jeroham, the son of Pelaliah, the son of Amzi, the son of Zechariah, the son of Pashhur, the son of Malchijah; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"and his associates, the leaders of families —  242 men  ; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Amashai son of Azarel, the son of Ahzai, the son of Meshillemoth, the son of Immer; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"and his associates ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Most LXX manuscripts; Hebrew <i>their associates</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"128   mighty men of valor. Zabdiel son of Haggedolim was their overseer . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"From the Levites: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Shemaiah son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam, the son of Hashabiah, the son of Bunni; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Shabbethai and Jozabad, two leaders of the Levites, who supervised the work outside the house of God; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Mattaniah son of Mica, the son of Zabdi, the son of Asaph, who led  in thanksgiving and prayer; Bakbukiah, second among his associates; and Abda son of Shammua, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"The Levites in the holy city totaled 284  . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"And the gatekeepers: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Akkub, Talmon, and their associates, who kept watch at the gates —  172 men  . "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Residents Outside Jerusalem"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"The rest of the Israelites, with the priests and Levites, were in all the villages of Judah, each on his own inheritance. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"The temple servants lived on the hill of Ophel, with Ziha and Gishpa over them. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Now the overseer of the Levites in Jerusalem was Uzzi son of Bani, the son of Hashabiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Mica. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Mica</i> is a variant of <i>Micaiah</i>; see Nehemiah 12:35."]}],"caller":"+"},"He was one of Asaph’s descendants, who were the singers in charge of the service of the house of God. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"For there was a command from the king concerning the singers, an ordinance regulating their daily  activities. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Pethahiah son of Meshezabel, a descendant of Zerah son of Judah, was the king’s agent ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>hand</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"in every matter concerning the people. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"As for the villages with their fields, some of the people of Judah lived  in Kiriath-arba , Dibon , Jekabzeel, and their villages; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"in Jeshua, Moladah,  and Beth-pelet; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"}," in Hazar-shual;  in Beersheba and its villages; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"in Ziklag; in Meconah and its villages; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"}," in En-rimmon, Zorah, Jarmuth, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Zanoah, Adullam, and their villages; in Lachish and its fields; and in Azekah and its villages. So they settled  from Beersheba all the way to the Valley of Hinnom. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"The descendants of Benjamin from Geba lived in Michmash, Aija,  and Bethel with its villages; ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"in Anathoth, Nob, Ananiah, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Hazor, Ramah, Gittaim, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Hadid, Zeboim, Neballat, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"Lod, and Ono; and in the Valley of the Craftsmen. ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:35 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Hebrew <i>in Ge-harashim</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"And some divisions of the Levites of Judah settled in Benjamin. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Priests and Levites Who Returned"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Now these are the priests and Levites who went up with Zerubbabel son of Shealtiel and with Jeshua: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Seraiah, Jeremiah, Ezra, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Amariah, Malluch, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Malluch</i> is a variant of <i>Malluchi</i>; see verse 14."]}],"caller":"+"},"Hattush, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Shecaniah, Rehum, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Rehum</i> is a variant of <i>Harim</i>; see verse 15, Nehemiah 7:42, and Ezra 2:39."]}],"caller":"+"},"Meremoth, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Iddo, Ginnethon, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Many Hebrew manuscripts and Vulgate (see also verse 16); most MT manuscripts <i>Ginnethoi</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"Abijah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Mijamin, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Mijamin</i> is a variant of <i>Miniamin</i>; see verse 17."]}],"caller":"+"},"Maadiah, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Maadiah</i> is a variant of <i>Moadiah</i>; see verse 17."]}],"caller":"+"},"Bilgah, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Bilgah</i> is a variant of <i>Bilgai</i>; also in verse 18; see Nehemiah 10:8."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Shemaiah, Joiarib, Jedaiah, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, and Jedaiah. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["These were the leaders of the priests and their associates in the days of Jeshua. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"The Levites were Jeshua, Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Judah, and Mattaniah, who, with his associates, led the songs of thanksgiving. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Bakbukiah and Unni, their associates, stood across from them in the services. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Jeshua was the father of  Joiakim, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Joiakim was the father of  Eliashib, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Eliashib  was the father of Joiada, "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Joiada was the father of  Jonathan, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Jonathan</i> is a variant of <i>Johanan</i>; see verse 22."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and Jonathan was the father of  Jaddua. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"In the days of Joiakim, these were the heads of the priestly families: "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of the family of Seraiah, Meraiah; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of Jeremiah, Hananiah; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"of Ezra, Meshullam; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of Amariah, Jehohanan; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"of Malluchi, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Malluchi</i> is a variant of <i>Malluch</i>; see verse 2."]}],"caller":"+"},"Jonathan; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of Shebaniah, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Shebaniah</i> is a variant of <i>Shecaniah</i>; see verse 3; see also Syriac and some Hebrew and LXX manuscripts."]}],"caller":"+"},"Joseph; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"of Harim, Adna; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of Meraioth, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Meraioth</i> is a variant of <i>Meremoth</i>; see verse 3 and also some LXX manuscripts."]}],"caller":"+"},"Helkai; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"of Iddo, Zechariah; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of Ginnethon, Meshullam; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"of Abijah, Zichri; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of Miniamin and of Moadiah, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Moadiah</i> is a variant of <i>Maadiah</i>; see verse 5."]}],"caller":"+"},"Piltai; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"of Bilgah, Shammua; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of Shemaiah, Jonathan; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"of Joiarib, Mattenai; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of Jedaiah, Uzzi; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"of Sallai, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:20 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Sallai</i> is a variant of <i>Sallu</i>; see verse 7."]}],"caller":"+"},"Kallai; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["of Amok, Eber; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"of Hilkiah, Hashabiah; "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and of Jedaiah, Nethanel. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"In the days of Eliashib, Joiada, Johanan, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Johanan</i> is a variant of <i>Jonathan</i>; see verse 11."]}],"caller":"+"},"and Jaddua, during the reign of Darius the Persian, the heads of the families of the Levites and priests were recorded. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"As for the descendants of Levi, the family heads up to the days of Johanan son of Eliashib were recorded in the Book of the Chronicles . ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:23 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the Book of the Annals</i> or <i>the Book of the Historical Events</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"The leaders of the Levites were Hashabiah, Sherebiah, and Jeshua son of Kadmiel, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>Sherebiah, Jeshua, Binnui, and Kadmiel</i>"]}],"caller":"+"},"along with their associates, who stood across from them to give praise and thanksgiving as one section alternated with the other, as prescribed by David the man of God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Mattaniah, Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon, and Akkub were gatekeepers who guarded  the storerooms at the gates. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"They served in the days of Joiakim son of Jeshua, the son of Jozadak, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Jozadak</i> is a variant of <i>Jehozadak</i>; see 1 Chronicles 6:14."]}],"caller":"+"},"and in the days of Nehemiah the governor and Ezra the priest and scribe. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Dedication of the Wall"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"At the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem, the Levites were sought out  from all their homes and brought to Jerusalem to celebrate the joyous dedication with thanksgiving and singing, accompanied by cymbals, harps, and lyres. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"}," The singers were also assembled from the region around Jerusalem, from the villages of the Netophathites, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"from Beth-gilgal , and from the fields of Geba and Azmaveth, for they had built villages for themselves around Jerusalem. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"After the priests and Levites had purified themselves, they purified  the people,  the gates,  and the wall. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Then I brought the leaders of Judah up  on the wall, and I appointed two great thanksgiving choirs. One was to proceed along the top of the wall ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:31 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>alongside the wall</i>; also in verse 38"]}],"caller":"+"},"to the right, toward the Dung Gate. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Hoshaiah and half the leaders of Judah followed , ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"along with Azariah, Ezra, Meshullam, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Judah, Benjamin, Shemaiah, Jeremiah, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"and some of the priests  with trumpets, and also Zechariah son of Jonathan, the son of Shemaiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Micaiah, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:35 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["<i>Micaiah</i> is a variant of <i>Mica</i>; see Nehemiah 11:22."]}],"caller":"+"},"the son of Zaccur, the son of Asaph, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"and his associates— Shemaiah, Azarel, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethanel, Judah, and Hanani— with the musical instruments prescribed by David the man of God. Ezra the scribe led the procession. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"At the Fountain  Gate they went directly up  the steps of the City of David on the ascent to the wall and passed above the house of David to the Water Gate on the east. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"The second thanksgiving choir proceeded to the left, and I followed it with half the people along the top of the wall, past the Tower of the Ovens to the Broad Wall, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"over the Gate of Ephraim,  the Jeshanah Gate, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:39 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or <i>the Old City Gate</i>"]}],"caller":"+"}," the Fish Gate, the Tower of Hananel, and the Tower of the Hundred, as far as the Sheep Gate. And they stopped at the Gate of the Guard. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"The two thanksgiving choirs then stood in the house of God, as did I, along with the half of the officials accompanying me, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"as well as the priests with their trumpets —  Eliakim, Maaseiah, Miniamin, Micaiah, Elioenai, Zechariah, and Hananiah —  ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"and also Maaseiah, Shemaiah, Eleazar, Uzzi, Jehohanan, Malchijah, Elam, and Ezer. Then the choirs sang out under the direction of Jezrahiah. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"On that day they offered great sacrifices, rejoicing because God had given them great joy . The women and children also rejoiced, so that the joy of Jerusalem was heard from afar. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Provisions for Temple Worship"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"And on that same day men were appointed over the rooms that housed the supplies, contributions, firstfruits, and tithes. The portions specified by the Law for the priests and Levites were gathered into these storerooms from the fields of the villages, because Judah rejoiced over the priests  and Levites who were serving. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"They performed the service of their God and the service of purification, along with the singers and gatekeepers, as David and his son Solomon had prescribed. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"For long ago, in the days of David and Asaph, there were directors for the singers and for the songs of praise and thanksgiving to God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"So in the days of Zerubbabel and Nehemiah, all Israel contributed the daily portions for the singers and gatekeepers. They also set aside daily  portions for the Levites, and the Levites set aside daily portions for the descendants of Aaron. "]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Foreigners Excluded"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"At that time the Book of Moses was read aloud in the hearing of the people, and in it they found the passage stating that no Ammonite or Moabite should ever  enter the assembly of God, ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See Deuteronomy 23:3–6."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"because they had not met  the Israelites  with food and water, but had hired Balaam  to call down a curse against them although our God had turned the curse into a blessing) "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"As soon as the people heard  this law, they excluded from Israel all of foreign descent. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Temple Cleansed"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Now before this, Eliashib the priest, a relative of Tobiah, had been put in charge of the storerooms of the house of our God ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"and had prepared for Tobiah a large room where  they had previously stored  the grain offerings, the frankincense, the temple articles, and the tithes of grain, new wine, and oil prescribed for the Levites, singers, and gatekeepers, along with the contributions for the priests. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"While all this was happening, I was not in Jerusalem, because I had returned to Artaxerxes king of Babylon ",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Artaxerxes king of Persia is identified here as the king of Babylon because Persia had conquered the Babylonian Empire."]}],"caller":"+"},"in the thirty-second  year of his reign. Some time later  I obtained leave from the king ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"to return to Jerusalem. Then I discovered the evil that Eliashib had done on behalf of Tobiah by providing him a room in the courts of the house of God. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"And I was greatly displeased and threw  all of Tobiah’s household goods out of the room. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Then I ordered that the rooms be purified, and I had the articles of the house of God  restored to them, along with the grain offerings and frankincense. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Tithes Restored"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../leviticus/27.htm#30|>Leviticus 27:30–34</a>; <a href =|../deuteronomy/14.htm#22|>Deuteronomy 14:22–29</a>; <a href =|../deuteronomy/26.htm|>Deuteronomy 26:1–15</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"I also learned that because the portions for the Levites had not been given to them, all the Levites and singers responsible for performing the service had gone back to their own fields. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"So I rebuked the officials and asked, Why has the house of God been neglected? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then I gathered the Levites and singers together and stationed them at their posts, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"and all Judah brought a tenth of the grain, new wine, and oil into the storerooms. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"I appointed as treasurers over the storerooms Shelemiah the priest, Zadok the scribe, and Pedaiah of the Levites, with Hanan son of Zaccur, the son of Mattaniah, to assist them, because they were considered trustworthy. They were responsible for distributing the supplies to their fellow Levites. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Remember me for this, O my God, and do not blot out my deeds of loving devotion   for the house of my God and for its services. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>The Sabbath Restored"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../jeremiah/17.htm#19|>Jeremiah 17:19–27</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"In those days I saw people in Judah treading winepresses on the Sabbath and bringing in grain and loading it on donkeys, along with wine, grapes, and figs. All kinds of goods were being brought into Jerusalem on the Sabbath day. So I warned them against selling food on that day. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Additionally, men of Tyre who lived there were importing fish and all kinds of merchandise and selling them on the Sabbath to the people of Judah in Jerusalem. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Then I rebuked  the nobles of Judah and asked What  is this  evil you are doing— profaning  the Sabbath day? ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Did not your forefathers do the same things, so that our God brought all this disaster on us  and on this city? And now you are rekindling His wrath against Israel by profaning  the Sabbath! "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"}," When the evening shadows began to fall on the gates of Jerusalem, just before the Sabbath, I ordered that the gates   be shut and not opened until after the Sabbath. I posted some of my servants at the gates so that no load could enter on the Sabbath day. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Once or twice, the merchants and those who sell all kinds of goods camped outside Jerusalem, ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"but I warned them  , Why are you camping in front of the wall? If you do it again, I will lay hands on you. From that time on, they did not return on the Sabbath. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Then I instructed the Levites   to purify themselves  and guard the gates in order to keep the Sabbath day holy.  "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Remember me for this as well, O my God, and show me mercy according to Your abundant loving devotion. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["<p class=|hdg|>Intermarriage Forbidden"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["<br /><span class=|cross|>(<a href =|../ezra/9.htm|>Ezra 9:1–4</a>)</span>"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"In those days I also saw  Jews who had married women from Ashdod, Ammon, and Moab. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Half of their children spoke the language of Ashdod or of the other peoples,  but could not speak the language of Judah. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"I rebuked them  and called down curses on them. I beat some of these men and pulled out their hair. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then I made them take an oath before God and said, You must not give your daughters in marriage to their sons  or take their daughters as wives for your sons or for yourselves! ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Did not King Solomon of Israel sin in matters like this? There was not a king like him among many nations, and he was loved by his God, who made him king over all Israel— yet foreign women  drew him into sin. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"}," Must we now hear that you too are doing  all this terrible evil and acting unfaithfully against our God by marrying foreign women? "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Even one of the sons of Jehoiada son of Eliashib the high priest had become a son-in-law to Sanballat the Horonite. Therefore I drove him away from me. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Remember them, O my God, because they have defiled the priesthood and the covenant of the priesthood and of the Levites. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Thus I purified the priests and Levites from everything foreign, and I assigned specific duties to each of the priests and Levites. ",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"I also arranged for contributions of wood at the appointed times, and for the firstfruits. "]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Remember me, O my God, with favor. "]}]}